# Cursor/Codex AI Rules for BIMAgent

## Guidelines
- Write modern, async Python 3.12+ code for the orchestration API.
- Use `google.antigravity` SDK constructs (`LocalAgentConfig`, `@hooks`, `enable_subagents=True`).
- Follow the Tri-Modal routing patterns described in the BIMRAG implementation plan.
- Ensure strict type-hinting and robust error recovery (`@hooks.on_tool_error`).

## Task List
- Read `TASKS.md` for 7 detailed tasks with specs and implementation steps.

## Model Routing
- Before any task, read `ROUTING.md` to select the correct model tier.
- Flash tier (offload 3–5): DeepSeek V4 Flash — bounded implementations.
- Flash→Pro tier (offload 5–7): Flash writes implementation, Pro reviews.
- Pro tier (offload > 7): DeepSeek V4 Pro — architecture, planning, debugging.
- Never send API keys or secrets to any model — use local Nanbeige-3B for sensitive material.
